[The warning should perhaps be extended to include passengers on the outward
flight to Kinshasa on 11 Sep 2003, although the risk of transmission in the
pre-symptomatic stage of measles infection will be very much less but not
negligible. - Mod.CP]
[ProMED-mail would like to thank Johann M van den Heever for sending
this information to ProMED for dissemination. In 2001, there was a
report of imported cases of measles in Mexico with presumed exposure
in an airport in Texas en route to Mexico (the presumed exposure was
to a tour group from Korea at a time when there was known measles
transmission ongoing in South Korea.-- see ProMED-mail postings
referenced below) This current alert and the prior events serve as a
reminder that measles virus is still circulating in parts of the
world, and vaccinations should be up to date prior to embarking on
travel. - Mod.MPP]
